# HDC automation

- Prefer the repo CLI as `hdc` from the repo root (`hdc.cmd` on Windows, `./hdc` on Unix after chmod). Do not tell operators to run `hdc` in docs, examples, or chat. Do not invent hostnames, IPs, or credentials.
- **Clump packages:** Live under the external **hdc-clumps** repo (or `~/.hdc/clump-repos/` after `hdc clumps init`). Bootstrap: `hdc clumps init`. Package scripts import shared runtime via `hdc/package/*` (`apps/hdc-cli/lib/package/`).
- **Static IP planning:** Read `hdc-private/operations/ip-allocations.md` for IP group boundaries and next-free addresses; cross-check `clumps/services/bind/config.json` and `operations/inventory/systems/*.json` before assigning. Do not store literal site IPs in the public hdc repo.
- **Greenfield service deploy:** Follow `.cursor/skills/hdc-service-deploy/SKILL.md` â€” ask discovery questions, write `plan.md` in hdc-private, get approval, then deploy and fix scripts; optional bind/nginx-waf/cloudflare only with user consent.
- **Private operator data:** Clump `config.json`, clump `.env`, and `operations/inventory` / `operations/automated` JSON live in the sibling **hdc-private** repo (or `HDC_PRIVATE_ROOT` in root `.env`) with the same paths as hdc. Resolution: public hdc file first, then hdc-private (both layers merge for `.env`). Global root `.env` holds vault/secret-backend only; clump `.env` loads on `hdc run` / daily maintain for that package. Helpers: `apps/hdc-cli/lib/private-repo.mjs`, `apps/hdc-cli/lib/clump-config.mjs`, `apps/hdc-cli/lib/clump-env.mjs`, `apps/hdc-cli/lib/package/clump-run-config.mjs`.
- Structured facts live in `operations/inventory/{systems,networks,services,targets}/` as `*.json` (in hdc-private for production; only `operations/inventory/systems/_example.json` in the public repo) (`kind`: `system`, `network`, `target`, or `services`). **System** records may list **`services`**: `{ "id": "<id>", "nodes"?: ["â€¦"] }` pointing at **`kind: "services"`** sidecars under `operations/inventory/services/` (by `id` only, no inline service payload). Use **`kind` `target`** plus required **`automation_target`** (manifest id) for per-plugin sidecar data. Schemas under `apps/hdc-cli/schema/inventory.*.schema.json`. Auth fields reference **env var names** only (for example `HDC_PROXMOX_SSH_USER`), never secret values.
- **System ids:** follow `.cursor/rules/hdc-inventory-naming.mdc` â€” class prefix (`vm-`, *(none)*, â€¦) for non-physical systems; physical hosts unprefixed; instance letters (`-a`, `-b`) not numbers.
- Never commit or paste `.env` contents. After changing inventory JSON, run `hdc docs lint` (or `docs sync` for the same checks). Optional companion `.md` files are not read or written by hdc.
- **Packages** (plugins) live under hdc-clumps `{infrastructure,services,clients}/<id>/manifest.json` with `deploy/`, `maintain/`, and `query/` scripts (`run.mjs`). **Home clients:** `clients/{windows,ubuntu,raspberrypi}/` each with its own `config.json` (`hdc run client windows maintain`, `hdc run client client-ubuntu query`, â€¦). Plugins may shell out to Ansible, Terraform, or SSH; orchestration stays in Node.
- **Logging:** For `hdc run <tier> <clump> â€¦ query|deploy`, log user-visible progress on **stderr** only; keep **stdout** clean for JSON when the CLI parses it. See `.cursor/rules/hdc-automation-logging.mdc` (required checks for package `*.mjs` changes).
- **QEMU guest agent:** For Proxmox **QEMU** deploy paths (not LXC), enable `agent=1` after clone and install `qemu-guest-agent` in the guest when SSH is available. See [`.cursor/rules/proxmox-qemu-guest-agent.mdc`](proxmox-qemu-guest-agent.mdc).
- **Guest maintain baseline:** Service `maintain` on Linux Proxmox guests ensures the `hdc` automation user (per-system `HDC_USER_HDC_PASSWORD_<SYSTEM_ID>` in vault, SSH keys, passwordless sudo), local sudo admin (`HDC_ADMIN_USER` in `.env`, `HDC_ADMIN_USER_PASSWORD` in vault), ClamAV + staggered scan timer, `unattended-upgrades`, CrowdSec/Wazuh agents (from `clumps/infrastructure/proxmox/config.json` `provision.guest_agents`), mail relay, and disables root SSH when both users succeed. Guest SSH defaults to `hdc` with auto-fallback to `root` (`HDC_GUEST_SSH_USER`, `hdc/package/guest-ssh-resolve.mjs`, `hdc/package/guest-ssh-exec.mjs`). Flags: `--skip-hdc-user`, `--skip-hdc-ssh-keys`, `--skip-admin-user`, `--skip-clamav`, `--skip-clamav-scan`, `--skip-unattended-upgrades`, `--skip-crowdsec-agent`, `--skip-wazuh-agent`, `--skip-mail-relay`, `--skip-disable-root`.
- **Masked secrets:** Vault passphrases, `hdc secrets set` values, and `getSecret()` prompts use **`readLineQuestion(q, { mask: true })`** (TTY raw mode, `*` echo) via `apps/hdc-cli/lib/readline-masked.mjs`. Non-TTY falls back to visible input with a warning.
- **Selective maintain filters:** Flags like `--site` (nginx / nginx-waf), `--rule` (unifi-network), or `--zone` (cloudflare) must not implicitly delete unrelated live resources. Use explicit `--prune` (or full maintain without a site filter) when removal is intended.
- **No root scratch scripts (`tmp-*`):** Never create `tmp-*` (or similar one-off scratch: `.mjs`, `.py`, `.sh`, `.json`, logs) at the **repo root** of `hdc` or `hdc-private`. Prefer `hdc run â€¦` and existing clump flags first (`proxmox query|maintain|teardown` e.g. `--guest`, `--find-template`, `--host-capacity`, `--migrate`, `--repair-console`, `--regen-cloudinit`, `--vmid â€¦ --any-node --purge --yes`; package `query --live` / `nginx-waf query --failing-only`). When a one-off helper is unavoidable, put it only under `tools/scripts/tmp-<short-purpose>.mjs` (or `.py`) â€” gitignored. Durable operator utilities use `tools/scripts/<descriptive-name>.mjs` (no `tmp-` prefix). Prefer extending hdc-clumps over new tools scripts; delete `tools/scripts/tmp-*` when the gap is closed. Root `/tmp-*` and `/tools/scripts/tmp-*` are gitignored.
- **Agent knowledge (OKF):** Start recall at `hdc-private/ai-docs/index.md` (only OKF bundle). After a durable learning, promote there per `.cursor/rules/hdc-okf-ai-docs.mdc` and skill `hdc-okf`; human prose stays under `docs/`.
